rComments: Fong's lectures are all over the place and he constantly brings in things from pop-culture that have little/no relevance to the topic at hand (i.e. watching a Beyonce music video when discussing a Victorian feminist text; discussing movies, tv shows, etc.) More focused on irrelevant discussion than actual lecturing. Had to use sparknotes, a lot.
Most professional, articulate, and passionate prof I've had in English. For those who think his quizzes are unfair...they probably shouldn't be taking the class.

He is so cute and fun. He is wayyyy heavy on the theory and he lets the same people participate the whole time but he is really passionate and cares about students. I think we were his first class that he wasn't just a TA for and he did a great job. I was really impressed. The midterm and the paper sucked but the final exam was not bad at all.
Such a great, intelligent guy. Take his classes!
